
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes to the current node set. It retrieves nodes using [get-nodes] from the [.arguments] node, specifically targeting [limit] and [offset] nodes, and adds them to the node set referenced by [data.read]. This is useful for dynamically constructing a node set based on input arguments.
add:x:./*/data.read
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/limit
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/offset
